text: According to God's Word "hell" is translated from the Hebrew word She'ol (in Greek it was rendered "hades"). She'ol means grave and its extensive use in the Bible relates to the common grave of mankind; in other words it has nothing to do with a place of eternal suffering where condemned people go after they die. Dante's Inferno isn't about literal "hell" - as many people see it - but rather a manifestation of Dante's pains the deeper up in high society he went. In other words it is a very imaginative illustration.
